But now I know.

38:05.050 --> 38:07.041
I've seen these
exact same markings before.

38:10.850 --> 38:12.408
This is ridiculous.

38:12.450 --> 38:14.384
H-How did you even
get a warrant?

38:14.420 --> 38:15.978
We looked
through the trash

38:16.020 --> 38:18.523
you put out on the curb
last night, Mr. Lima.

38:18.560 --> 38:20.824
We found pet store receipts
that show you purchased

38:20.860 --> 38:22.555
the supplies needed to house

38:22.600 --> 38:24.818
and feed
a coastal taipan.

38:24.870 --> 38:26.724
WATSON: The venom
from that species

38:26.770 --> 38:29.568
poisoned seven people
at Arrondissement 21

38:29.600 --> 38:31.909
and killed your friend
Brian Beale.

38:31.940 --> 38:34.807
I don't even know who that is.

38:34.840 --> 38:36.933
Sure you do. You went
to Gracely High together.

38:36.980 --> 38:39.574
You signed his yearbook.
We found it at his apartment.

38:39.610 --> 38:40.599
Go Tigers.

38:40.650 --> 38:41.969
BELL: You also got
a parking ticket

38:42.020 --> 38:43.669
down the block
from the restaurant

38:43.720 --> 38:46.484
at 3:15 am. on the night
the place was broken into.

38:46.520 --> 38:48.408
HOLMES: We're certain that you
were the burglar that evening.

38:48.460 --> 38:49.984
You staged a robbery
at your own kitchen

38:50.020 --> 38:51.624
to throw suspicion
off other members

38:51.660 --> 38:53.082
of staff such as yourself.

38:53.130 --> 38:55.598
I ate some of that foie gras,
remember?

38:55.630 --> 38:57.120
I was sick
for two days.

38:57.160 --> 38:59.697
Now, why in the hell
would I dose myself

38:59.730 --> 39:01.368
with snake venom?

39:01.400 --> 39:02.731
Because you're immune.
HOLMES: As you well know,

39:02.770 --> 39:03.794
there's a process

39:03.840 --> 39:05.398
called mithridatism.

39:05.440 --> 39:07.362
It's named after
King Mithridates VI,

39:07.410 --> 39:08.672
ruler of ancient Pontus.

39:08.710 --> 39:10.439
He was so afraid
of being poisoned

39:10.480 --> 39:12.948
that he would regularly
ingest very small doses

39:12.980 --> 39:16.472
of various toxins in order
to build up an immunity.

39:18.020 --> 39:20.841
I-I think you may have seen
The Princess Bride

39:20.890 --> 39:22.551
one too many times.

39:22.590 --> 39:24.854
Except that iocane powder
is fictional.

39:24.890 --> 39:27.051
Immunizing yourself
against snake venom

39:27.090 --> 39:29.092
is a scientific reality.

39:29.130 --> 39:31.462
Last night, I had
the opportunity to examine

39:31.500 --> 39:33.718
the jaws
of a coastal taipan.

39:33.770 --> 39:35.658
I realized that
the scars on your hands,

39:35.700 --> 39:38.567
scars I initially attributed
to your work as a line cook,

39:38.610 --> 39:40.862
were in fact a perfect match

39:40.910 --> 39:42.832
for the taipan's
symmetrical bite pattern.

39:42.880 --> 39:44.541
And it makes sense
that you've been bitten.

39:44.580 --> 39:45.547
You'd been
handling that snake

39:45.580 --> 39:48.140
for months, milking it
to draw out its venom.

39:48.180 --> 39:49.977
Hard work pays off.

39:50.020 --> 39:51.749
You managed to poison
the key-holder lunch

39:51.790 --> 39:52.916
Without anybody looking

39:52.950 --> 39:53.917
in your direction.

39:53.950 --> 39:55.178
And it set up
your next play--

39:55.220 --> 39:58.053
robbing those paintings
from the stock exchange.

39:58.090 --> 39:59.785
You got too greedy

39:59.830 --> 40:02.025
when you decided not to share
with Brian, though.

40:02.060 --> 40:05.461
Up until that point,
pretty tight plan.

40:05.500 --> 40:08.936
MATEO:
All your, uh... evidence

40:08.970 --> 40:10.790
is circumstantial.

40:10.840 --> 40:13.058
I mean...

40:13.110 --> 40:15.806
I went to high school
with Brian Beale.

40:15.840 --> 40:18.206
So did 900 other people.

40:18.240 --> 40:20.549
And, yeah, I got
a parking ticket that night.

40:20.580 --> 40:23.219
That happened a half a dozen
other nights, too.

40:23.250 --> 40:25.946
I leave my car at work
and take the subway home

40:25.990 --> 40:28.550
ifI have too much
to drink after hours.

40:28.590 --> 40:30.979
You may have had enough
for a... a warrant,

40:31.020 --> 40:34.456
but if you had enough to arrest
me, you already would have.

40:35.900 --> 40:37.458
I'm right, aren't I?

40:37.500 --> 40:38.797
We're not quite ready to answer

40:38.830 --> 40:41.094
that question just yet,
Mr. Lima.

40:41.130 --> 40:43.860
Uh, what are you doing?

40:43.900 --> 40:47.063
Something's preventing the water
from soaking into the soil here.

40:47.110 --> 40:48.839
Don't worry.

40:48.880 --> 40:51.075
Tree pythons are...

40:51.110 --> 40:52.941
nocturnal, right?

40:52.980 --> 40:54.641
I think.

41:03.760 --> 41:05.159
(chuckles)

41:05.190 --> 41:06.828
I have to give you credit

41:06.860 --> 41:08.521
for devising
such a clever hiding place,

41:08.560 --> 41:10.221
Mr. Lima.

41:10.260 --> 41:13.525
He will be arresting you now.

41:15.640 --> 41:17.198
(footsteps approaching)

41:17.240 --> 41:21.006
WATSON: Oh, there you are.
I just heard from Marcus.

41:21.040 --> 41:22.837
The curator at the Whitney
took a look at the painting

41:22.880 --> 41:24.199
you found
in the python terrarium.

41:24.240 --> 41:25.741
It's the real McCoy.

41:25.780 --> 41:27.247
Or LeGrand, as it were.

41:27.280 --> 41:28.975
That's one down.

41:29.020 --> 41:30.942
Actually, the other two
should be recovered soon.

41:30.980 --> 41:33.540
Mateo Lima's case went federal.
He took a deal

41:33.590 --> 41:35.683
and gave up the name
of the guy who bought them.

41:35.720 --> 41:37.585
Wise move.
The US. government

41:37.620 --> 41:40.828
could inject him with poisons
he's not inoculated against.

41:40.860 --> 41:43.021
I'm going out for coffee.
You want to join?

41:43.060 --> 41:46.291
I can't. I have a
video chat with Fiona.

41:46.330 --> 41:50.130
You know, I bet she'd love
to hear about this case.

41:50.170 --> 41:52.638
(computer chiming)

41:52.670 --> 41:55.173
Enjoy your coffee, Watson.

41:59.850 --> 42:01.818
(sighs)

